main event: On July 25, 1955, a civilian observed a round object that appeared as a red glare and seemed to be hovering in the northwest, 20 miles northwest of Minneapolis, Minnesota.
interesting points: The object was described as round and appeared as a red glare, similar to a light bulb.
It seemed to be hovering in the northwest.
The report indicates that there were no photographs of the observed object.
The source of the observation was a civilian, adding to the credibility of the report.
The conclusion was marked as 'Insufficient Data for Evaluation', suggesting a lack of concrete explanation for the sighting.
